text: Wick in Caithness was a royal burgh that returned one commissioner to the Parliament of Scotland and to the Convention of Estates. After the Acts of Union 1707, Wick, Dingwall, Dornoch, Kirkwall and Tain formed the Tain district of burghs, returning one member between them to the House of Commons of Great Britain. ==List of burgh commissioners== * 1661: William McBaith, merchant-burgessFoster, p. 223. *1665 convention, 1667 convention, 1669–74: no representation * 1678 convention, 1681–82, 1685–86: Alexander Manson, merchant, bailieFoster, p. 241. * 1690–1701: Sir Archibald SinclairG. E. C., The Complete Baronetage, vol. III (1903) p. 351. * 1702–07: Robert FraserFoster, p. 144. ==References== * Joseph Foster, Members of Parliament, Scotland (1882). ==See also== * List of constituencies in the Parliament of Scotland at the time of the Union Category:Constituencies of the Parliament of Scotland (to 1707) Category:Constituencies disestablished in 1707 Category:Wick, Caithness Category:1707 disestablishments in Scotland
title: Wick (Parliament of Scotland constituency)
